commit.message: Version 1.3.1

Unroll 2-item map

It's slightly faster, and easier to read.

Return max distance when string is empty

Previously, comparing any string with an empty string would return the
full distance, without limiting it to the maximum.

Improve consistency of similar code

This code is duplicated for efficiency, but it should look the same.

Version 1.3.0

Adds maximum distance optimisation for Levenshtein.
Removes support for Ruby versions before 1.9.

Constrain Rake version so gem is happy

Eliminates a warning (and probably makes things more reliable in
future).

Add licence to gem

Closes #20.
Remove unecessary branch
Return nil for uncodable strings
Use Ruby's built-in string padding

Ignore non-A-Z in input to Soundex

Soundex is only defined for A-Z. Previously, coding an input containing
a space would give a result of nil.

Fixes issue #19.
Use yml ext for YAML test data
Move Soundex test data to file
Make benchmarking output prettier
Merge branch 'levenshtein_max_distance'
Benchmark Levenshtein with maximum

Use generated data to test Levenshtein

Mutate strings using insertion, deletion, and substition.

Optimise by dispatching early

Checking for max_distance results makes calculations take about 18%
longer when there's no maximum. Splitting it out into two methods
mitigates this.
Tweak spacing and remove unnecessary parens
Prefer if/else to ternary

Use a more common idiom for array initialisation

In addition, a < [b, c].min is the same as a < b || a < c, because if
it's less than the smaller, it'll definitely be less than the larger.
Expressing it this way is simpler, I think.
Avoid for

Be explicit when sorting is intended

It avoids duplication and makes the intention clearer.
Tweak comments and remove trailing space
Reduce second loop to 2k-1 (where k is max_distance), when max_distance is specified
Fix: Diagonal index was not correctly calculated in some special cases when levenshtein matrix was not square
Avoid iterate full word when the diagonal value is greater or equal to max_distance
Add failing tests for issue #15
